# Python Agent Conventions

## Architecture Layers (strict — no layer skipping)
- `domain/` — pure Pydantic models, no imports from other layers
- `services/` — business logic, depends on domain + repositories via interfaces
- `adapters/` — all I/O (GitHub, OpenRouter, Supabase); implement interfaces from domain
- `repositories/` — SQLAlchemy 2.0 async; depend only on domain models
- `api/` — FastAPI routers; call services only, never repositories or adapters directly

## Typing
- All public functions must have full type annotations
- Use `Pydantic v2` for domain models and LLM structured output
- Run `mypy --strict` before committing

## Async
- All I/O functions must be `async def`
- Use `asyncio.gather()` for parallelisable I/O, never sequential awaits in a loop

## Error Handling
```python
# ❌ BAD
raise Exception("something went wrong")

# ✅ GOOD — typed domain exception
raise AuditRunError("GitHub API returned 403", cause=e)
```

## Logging
```python
# ❌ BAD
print(f"Processing PR {pr_number}")

# ✅ GOOD — structured JSON via structlog
logger.info("audit.started", pr_number=pr_number, repo=repo_full_name)
```

## LLM Calls
- All LLM calls go through `adapters/openrouter.py`
- Response must be validated against a Pydantic model before use
- Log `tokens_used` and `cost_usd` on every call
